					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-731711#post-1900994</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-731711/scp-1953#post-1900994</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 24 Nov 2013 23:43:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>BlueRiging</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1760503</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Would love to know the thought process behind the idea of this SCP. Did you see the picture, and think: &quot;hm. Weird art. This could be an SCP&quot; but then thought about how it was created, &quot;oh, out of food items!&quot; but then thought &quot;oh, WHAT could have made it?&quot; after a period of time you came up with cockroaches, but then &quot;wait, where could they make it?&quot; &quot;F*ck it, the human stomach, and let's have them make tons, and have a weird way that they got there&#8230;&quot; so on and so forth. Yeah, the article feels random, but it it is <em>very</em> interesting.<br /> Take it: +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
